        Simulated sub-market grid — replace with actual STOC dataset segmented by zipcode cluster or census tract · Mid-Density bands applied (3 / 7 / 15 / 25 mi)
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Interpretation card -->
    <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:12px">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-hd">How to Read the White Space Map</div>
        <div class="card-body" style="padding:0">
          <div style="padding:10px 14px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-lt);display:flex;gap:10px;align-items:flex-start">
            <span class="sig sig-ws" style="flex-shrink:0;margin-top:1px">White Space</span>
            <span style="font-size:12px;color:var(--slate)">Low supply relative to addressable female 25–64 population. Primary de novo site candidate. No tuck-in competition in zone.</span>
          </div>
          <div style="padding:10px 14px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-lt);display:flex;gap:10px;align-items:flex-start">
            <span class="sig sig-ti" style="flex-shrink:0;margin-top:1px">Tuck-In</span>
            <span style="font-size:12px;color:var(--slate)">Moderate supply, existing operator in Zone 2 window. Acquisition candidate — extract value from established patient base without new-site capital.</span>
          </div>
          <div style="padding:10px 14px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-lt);display:flex;gap:10px;align-items:flex-start">
            <span class="sig sig-ci" style="flex-shrink:0;margin-top:1px">Monitor</span>
            <span style="font-size:12px;color:var(--slate)">Density approaching threshold. Track competition dynamics quarterly. Don't prioritize for new entry today.</span>
          </div>
          <div style="padding:10px 14px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-lt);display:flex;gap:10px;align-items:flex-start">
            <span class="sig sig-cr" style="flex-shrink:0;margin-top:1px">Saturated</span>
            <span style="font-size:12px;color:var(--slate)">Supply exceeds demand threshold for new entry. Existing operator acquisition only — and only if differentiated (services, premium positioning).</span>
          </div>
          <div style="padding:10px 14px;display:flex;gap:10px;align-items:flex-start">
            <span class="sig sig-em" style="flex-shrink:0;margin-top:1px">Emerging</span>
            <span style="font-size:12px;color:var(--slate)">Population growing faster than supply. Watch list — may shift to White Space within 12–18 months as population fills in.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="drive-note" style="border-left-color:var(--teal);background:var(--teal-lt)">
        <div class="drive-note-tag" style="color:var(--teal);background:rgba(13,138,122,0.12)">Key Insight</div>
        <div>The same CBSA can contain <strong>both saturated and white-space sub-markets simultaneously.</strong> Dallas–Fort Worth is a top-10 national market yet North Frisco and South Fort Worth are genuinely underserved. The CBSA-level view misses this — only the radius clustering model reveals it.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- OUTPUT 2: Ranked target list -->
  <div class="lbl-sm">Output 2 — Ranked Target List by Zone &amp; Outreach Priority</div>
  <div class="card" style="margin-bottom:16px">
    <div class="card-hd card-hd-navy">
      <span>Simulated Target MedSpas — Dallas–Fort Worth CBSA (Mid-Density Bands)</span>
      <span style="font-size:10px;color:var(--muted);font-weight:400">Sorted: Zone → Validation Score → Review Weakness</span>
    </div>
    <table class="out-table" id="targetTable">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="width:28px" class="thc">Pri.</th>
          <th>Opportunity Name</th>
          <th>Sub-Market</th>
          <th class="thc">Zone</th>
          <th class="thc">Dist. (mi)</th>
          <th class="thc">NN Count<br><span style="font-weight:400;opacity:0.6">in zone</span></th>
          <th class="thc">Val. Score</th>
          <th class="thc">Avg Rating</th>
          <th>Cannibal. Risk</th>
          <th>Signal</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody></tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- OUTPUTS 3+4: Cannibalization + Nearest Neighbor side by side -->
  <div class="g2">
    <div>
      <div class="lbl-sm">Output 3 — Cannibalization Risk Logic</div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-hd card-hd-navy">Risk Flag Criteria</div>
        <table class="dt-table">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Risk Level</th><th>Trigger Condition</th><th>Recommended Action</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><span class="cannibal-flag cf-high"><span class="cf-dot" style="background:var(--red)"></span>High</span></td>
              <td style="font-size:11.5px;color:var(--slate)">≥3 MedSpas in Zone 1 <em>and</em> same service mix overlap ≥60%</td>
              <td style="font-size:11.5px;color:var(--slate)">Pause acquisition. Conduct patient overlap analysis before proceeding.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><span class="cannibal-flag cf-med"><span class="cf-dot" style="background:var(--amber)"></span>Medium</span></td>
              <td style="font-size:11.5px;color:var(--slate)">1–2 MedSpas in Zone 1 <em>or</em> service overlap 30–60%</td>
              <td style="font-size:11.5px;color:var(--slate)">Proceed with caution. Differentiation strategy (services, price tier) required.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><span class="cannibal-flag cf-low"><span class="cf-dot" style="background:var(--green)"></span>Low</span></td>
              <td style="font-size:11.5px;color:var(--slate)">0 MedSpas in Zone 1, 1–3 in Zone 2, overlap &lt;30%</td>
              <td style="font-size:11.5px;color:var(--slate)">Clear for acquisition or de novo. Review quality/validation before outreach.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><span class="cannibal-flag cf-none"><span class="cf-dot" style="background:var(--muted)"></span>None</span></td>
              <td style="font-size:11.5px;color:var(--slate)">Zone 4 target — no overlap possible at current footprint</td>
              <td style="font-size:11.5px;color:var(--slate)">White space confirmed. De novo site evaluation or anchor acquisition.</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <div style="padding:8px 12px;font-size:10.5px;color:var(--muted);font-style:italic;background:var(--bg);border-top:1px solid var(--border-lt)">
          * Service overlap derived from Top 3 Services field in STOC dataset — already captured, no enrichment needed
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div>
      <div class="lbl-sm">Output 4 — Nearest-Neighbor Count by Zone</div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-hd card-hd-navy">NN Density — What the Count Tells You</div>
        <div class="card-body" style="padding:0">
          <div style="padding:10px 14px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-lt)">
            <div style="font-size:9px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:0.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:8px">Zone 1 Nearest-Neighbor Count Interpretation</div>
            <div id="nnBars" style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:8px"></div>
          </div>
          <div style="padding:10px 14px">
            <div style="font-size:9px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:0.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:8px">Zone 2 NN Count — Tuck-In Density Signal</div>
            <div id="nnBars2" style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:8px"></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div style="padding:8px 12px;font-size:10.5px;color:var(--muted);font-style:italic;background:var(--bg);border-top:1px solid var(--border-lt)">
          Thresholds are CBSA-density adjusted · Mid-density shown above · Dense Urban thresholds are ~40% lower
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

</div><!-- /page -->

<!-- ══ METHODOLOGY FOOTER ═══════════════════════════════ -->
<div class="method-footer">
  <div class="mf-item">
    <div class="mf-icon">Z</div>
    <div class="mf-text"><strong>Zone Bands</strong>Density-adjusted per CBSA tier. Dense Urban caps at 15 mi to avoid crossing CBSA boundary. No 20–50 mi bands.</div>
  </div>
  <div class="mf-item">
    <div class="mf-icon">H</div>
    <div class="mf-text"><strong>Haversine</strong>Great-circle distance. Lat/Long sourced directly from STOC dataset. Pairwise matrix across all records in CBSA.</div>
  </div>
  <div class="mf-item">
    <div class="mf-icon">W</div>
    <div class="mf-text"><strong>White Space</strong>Intra-CBSA supply gap — not platform-proximity. Measured against female 25–64 addressable population per sub-market.</div>
  </div>
  <div class="mf-item">
    <div class="mf-icon">C</div>
    <div class="mf-text"><strong>Cannibalization</strong>Zone 1 count + service mix overlap from Top 3 Services field. No enrichment needed — data already in STOC dataset.</div>
  </div>
  <div class="mf-item">
    <div class="mf-icon">N</div>
    <div class="mf-text"><strong>Nearest-Neighbor</strong>Count of MedSpas within each zone radius from reference point. Thresholds adjusted per density tier.</div>
  </div>
  <div style="margin-left:auto;font-size:10px;color:rgba(186,202,236,0.28);font-style:italic;align-self:flex-end">All CBSA data simulated for wireframe · Replace with STOC proprietary dataset</div>
</div>

<div class="doc-footer">
  <span>STOC Advisory · MedSpa Market Intelligence · Confidential · Model Component 02</span>
  <span>Radius-Based Target Clustering · February 2026</span>
</div>

<script>
/* ═══════════════════════════════════════
   DENSITY TIER DEFINITIONS
═══════════════════════════════════════ */
const TIERS = {
  dense: {
    label: 'Dense Urban',
    examples: 'NYC · LA · Chicago · SF · Boston',
    zones: [
      { num:1, color:'var(--z1)', colorLt:'var(--z1-lt)', tag:'Saturation Core',    miles:'0 – 2 mi',  drive:'≈5–8 min',  desc:'Direct overlap. High cannibalization risk. Avoid new supply unless patient volume analysis clears.' },
      { num:2, color:'var(--z2)', colorLt:'var(--z2-lt)', tag:'Tuck-In Zone',       miles:'2 – 5 mi',  drive:'≈10–12 min',desc:'Primary tuck-in candidates. Operational synergy possible. Expand addressable geography without full de novo risk.' },
      { num:3, color:'var(--z3)', colorLt:'var(--z3-lt)', tag:'Competitive Intel',  miles:'5 – 10 mi', drive:'≈15–20 min',desc:'Competitive density watch. Track emerging independents. Multiple subway/transit zones in NYC = distinct patient populations.' },
      { num:4, color:'var(--z4)', colorLt:'var(--z4-lt)', tag:'White Space Ring',   miles:'10 – 15 mi',drive:'≈20–30 min',desc:'Beyond saturation. De novo site candidates. Cap at 15 mi — beyond this you risk crossing into adjacent CBSA in dense markets.' },
    ],
    counts: [12, 8, 14, 5]
  },
  mid: {
    label: 'Mid-Density',
    examples: 'Dallas · Atlanta · Denver · Phoenix · Seattle',
    zones: [
      { num:1, color:'var(--z1)', colorLt:'var(--z1-lt)', tag:'Saturation Core',    miles:'0 – 3 mi',  drive:'≈6–10 min', desc:'Direct overlap zone. Existing supply captures most of the local addressable demand. Acquisition only if quality gap present.' },
      { num:2, color:'var(--z2)', colorLt:'var(--z2-lt)', tag:'Tuck-In Zone',       miles:'3 – 7 mi',  drive:'≈10–15 min',desc:'Ideal tuck-in window. Suburban neighborhoods, strip-mall corridors. Acquire established single-site operators here first.' },
      { num:3, color:'var(--z3)', colorLt:'var(--z3-lt)', tag:'Competitive Intel',  miles:'7 – 15 mi', drive:'≈15–25 min',desc:'Monitor zone. Understand which sub-markets are building supply. Check for emerging independents before they become targets.' },
      { num:4, color:'var(--z4)', colorLt:'var(--z4-lt)', tag:'White Space Ring',   miles:'15 – 25 mi',drive:'≈25–35 min',desc:'True white space. Fast-growing exurbs. Cap at 25 mi — beyond this, different population cluster, assess as separate sub-market.' },
    ],
    counts: [8, 12, 18, 7]
  },
  sub: {
    label: 'Suburban / Spread',
    examples: 'Nashville · Charlotte · Austin · Raleigh · Salt Lake',
    zones: [
      { num:1, color:'var(--z1)', colorLt:'var(--z1-lt)', tag:'Saturation Core',    miles:'0 – 5 mi',  drive:'≈8–12 min', desc:'Core zone. Meaningful overlap but spread population means cannibalization risk is lower than dense tiers. Still assess service mix.' },
      { num:2, color:'var(--z2)', colorLt:'var(--z2-lt)', tag:'Tuck-In Zone',       miles:'5 – 10 mi', drive:'≈12–18 min',desc:'Strong tuck-in zone. Residents in these markets are accustomed to 10–15 min drives for elective services. High operational synergy.' },
      { num:3, color:'var(--z3)', colorLt:'var(--z3-lt)', tag:'Competitive Intel',  miles:'10 – 20 mi',drive:'≈20–28 min',desc:'Outer competitive ring. These markets may be separate township identities (Franklin vs Nashville). Track independently.' },
      { num:4, color:'var(--z4)', colorLt:'var(--z4-lt)', tag:'White Space Ring',   miles:'20 – 30 mi',drive:'≈28–40 min',desc:'Adjacent sub-metros and fast-growing corridors. Cap at 30 mi — beyond this, separate market thesis required. Not a drive-time MedSpa patient.' },
    ],
    counts: [5, 9, 16, 11]
  }
};

let currentTier = 'dense';

function setTier(tier) {
  currentTier = tier;
  document.querySelectorAll('.ds-btn').forEach((b,i) => {
    b.classList.toggle('active', ['dense','mid','sub'][i] === tier);
  });
  renderZoneBands(tier);
  renderZoneCounts(tier);
}

function renderZoneBands(tier) {
  const t = TIERS[tier];
  const container = document.getElementById('zoneBands');
  container.innerHTML = t.zones.map(z => `
    <div class="zone-card" style="animation:fadeUp 0.3s ease both">
      <div class="zone-top" style="background:${z.color}"></div>
      <div class="zone-body">
        <div class="zone-label" style="color:${z.color}">Zone ${z.num} · ${t.label}</div>
        <div class="zone-range">${z.miles}</div>
        <div><span class="zone-tag" style="background:${z.colorLt};color:${z.color}">${z.tag}</span></div>
        <div style="font-size:10.5px;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:4px">${z.drive} drive-time equivalent</div>
        <div class="zone-desc">${z.desc}</div>
      </div>
    </div>`).join('');
}

function renderZoneCounts(tier) {
  const counts = TIERS[tier].counts;
  ['zc1','zc2','zc3','zc4'].forEach((id, i) => {
    document.getElementById(id).textContent = counts[i];
  });
}

/* ── Initial render ── */
renderZoneBands('dense');
renderZoneCounts('dense');

/* ═══════════════════════════════════════
   MAP SCATTER DOTS
═══════════════════════════════════════ */
// Simulated MedSpa positions on the ring map
const scatterDots = [
  // Zone 1 (core) — red
  { x:52, y:44, z:1 }, { x:48, y:56, z:1 }, { x:55, y:52, z:1 },
  { x:45, y:47, z:1 }, { x:52, y:48, z:1 },
  // Zone 2 (tuck-in) — amber
  { x:36, y:42, z:2 }, { x:62, y:38, z:2 }, { x:40, y:64, z:2 },
  { x:60, y:62, z:2 }, { x:66, y:50, z:2 }, { x:34, y:54, z:2 },
  // Zone 3 (competitive) — blue
  { x:26, y:44, z:3 }, { x:72, y:36, z:3 }, { x:30, y:62, z:3 },
  { x:68, y:66, z:3 }, { x:50, y:24, z:3 }, { x:50, y:76, z:3 },
  { x:74, y:52, z:3 }, { x:24, y:52, z:3 },
  // Zone 4 (white space) — green — sparse
  { x:18, y:50, z:4 }, { x:82, y:50, z:4 }, { x:50, y:16, z:4 },
  { x:50, y:84, z:4 }, { x:22, y:30, z:4 },
];

const zColors = { 1:'var(--z1)', 2:'var(--z2)', 3:'var(--z3)', 4:'var(--z4)' };
const mapRings = document.getElementById('mapRings');
scatterDots.forEach(d => {
  const dot = document.createElement('div');
  dot.className = 'scatter-dot';
  dot.style.cssText = `left:${d.x}%;top:${d.y}%;background:${zColors[d.z]};opacity:0.7`;
  mapRings.appendChild(dot);
});

/* ═══════════════════════════════════════
   TARGET TABLE DATA
=══════════════════════════════════════ */
const targets = [
  // [name, submarket, zone, dist, nnCount, valScore, rating, cannibal, signal]
  ["Glow Aesthetics DFW",     "North Frisco",        2, 4.1,  2,  88, 4.7, "low",  "tuck-in"],
  ["Revive MedSpa Southlake", "Southlake / Keller",  2, 5.8,  3,  84, 4.8, "low",  "tuck-in"],
  ["Aesthetica Prosper",      "North Frisco",        4, 16.2, 0,  76, 4.4, "none", "white-space"],
  ["Premier Skin Plano",      "Plano / Allen",       2, 6.4,  4,  91, 4.9, "low",  "tuck-in"],
  ["Luxe Laser & Skin",       "S. Fort Worth",       4, 18.8, 1,  72, 4.3, "none", "white-space"],
  ["Refresh MedSpa Allen",    "Plano / Allen",       3, 9.1,  6,  80, 4.6, "med",  "monitor"],
  ["Dallas Aesthetics Studio","Uptown Dallas",       1, 1.4, 12,  88, 4.8, "high", "core"],
  ["Highland Park Glow",      "Uptown Dallas",       1, 2.1, 14,  92, 4.9, "high", "core"],
  ["Contour Med & Wellness",  "S. Fort Worth",       4, 21.4, 0,  68, 4.1, "none", "white-space"],
  ["The MedSpa Collective",   "Plano / Allen",       2, 4.8,  3,  85, 4.5, "low",  "tuck-in"],
  ["Luxe Aesthetics Burleson","S. Fort Worth",       4, 23.1, 0,  62, 4.0, "none", "white-space"],
  ["Knox-Henderson Skin",     "Knox-Henderson",      1, 0.8, 18,  95, 4.9, "high", "core"],
];

const signalLabels = {
  'tuck-in':    ['sig-ti',  'Tuck-In'],
  'white-space':['sig-ws',  'White Space'],
  'monitor':    ['sig-ci',  'Monitor'],
  'core':       ['sig-cr',  'Saturation Core'],
};
const cannibalMap = {
  'high': ['cf-high', 'High', 'var(--red)'],
  'med':  ['cf-med',  'Medium', 'var(--amber)'],
  'low':  ['cf-low',  'Low', 'var(--green)'],
  'none': ['cf-none', 'None', 'var(--muted)'],
};
const zonePriority = { 2: 1, 4: 2, 3: 3, 1: 4 };

// Sort: zone 2 first (tuck-in), then 4 (white space), then 3, then 1
const sorted = [...targets].sort((a,b) => (zonePriority[a[2]]||5) - (zonePriority[b[2]]||5));

const tbody = document.querySelector('#targetTable tbody');
let pri = 1;
sorted.forEach((row, i) => {
  const [name, sub, zone, dist, nn, val, rat, canib, sig] = row;
  const [scls, slbl] = signalLabels[sig] || ['sig-ci','Monitor'];
  const [ccls, clbl, cdot] = cannibalMap[canib] || cannibalMap['none'];
  const isHighPri = zone === 2 || (zone === 4 && canib === 'none');
  const pBadge = zone === 2 ? `<span class="priority-badge p1">${pri++}</span>` :
                 zone === 4 ? `<span class="priority-badge p2">${pri++}</span>` :
                 zone === 3 ? `<span class="priority-badge p3">—</span>` :
                              `<span class="priority-badge pn">✕</span>`;

  const nnMax = 18;
  const nnWidth = Math.min((nn/nnMax)*100, 100);
  const nnColor = nn<=3?'var(--green)':nn<=8?'var(--blue)':nn<=14?'var(--amber)':'var(--red)';

  tbody.innerHTML += `
    <tr>
      <td class="tdc">${pBadge}</td>
      <td style="font-weight:600;color:var(--navy)">${name}</td>
      <td style="font-size:11.5px;color:var(--slate)">${sub}</td>
      <td class="tdc">
        <span style="font-weight:700;color:${['','var(--z1)','var(--z2)','var(--z3)','var(--z4)'][zone]}">Z${zone}</span>
      </td>
      <td class="tdc" style="font-variant-numeric:tabular-nums;color:var(--slate)">${dist.toFixed(1)}</td>
      <td>
        <div class="nn-cell">
          <div class="nn-track"><div class="nn-fill" style="width:${nnWidth}%;background:${nnColor}"></div></div>
          <span class="nn-val" style="color:${nnColor}">${nn}</span>
        </div>
      </td>
      <td class="tdc" style="font-weight:600;color:${val>=85?'var(--blue)':val>=70?'var(--indigo)':'var(--muted)'}">${val}</td>
      <td class="tdc" style="font-weight:600;color:${rat>=4.7?'var(--green)':rat>=4.3?'var(--blue)':'var(--amber)'}">${rat.toFixed(1)}★</td>
      <td>
        <div class="cannibal-flag ${ccls}">
          <span class="cf-dot" style="background:${cdot}"></span>
          ${clbl}
        </div>
      </td>
      <td><span class="sig ${scls}">${slbl}</span></td>
    </tr>`;
});

/* ═══════════════════════════════════════
   NEAREST-NEIGHBOR BARS
=══════════════════════════════════════ */
function renderNNBars(containerId, rows) {
  const el = document.getElementById(containerId);
  el.innerHTML = rows.map(([lbl, val, max, color, interp]) => `
    <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;margin-bottom:2px">
      <span style="min-width:72px;font-size:11px;color:var(--slate)">${lbl}</span>
      <div class="nn-track" style="flex:1;height:6px">
        <div class="nn-fill" style="width:${Math.min(val/max*100,100)}%;background:${color}"></div>
      </div>
      <span style="min-width:14px;font-weight:700;font-size:12px;color:${color}">${val}</span>
      <span style="font-size:10.5px;color:var(--muted);min-width:90px">${interp}</span>
    </div>`).join('');
}

renderNNBars('nnBars', [
  ['0 locations', 0,  10, 'var(--green)',  '✓ White space confirmed'],
  ['1–2 locs.',   2,  10, 'var(--blue)',   'Low risk · Proceed'],
  ['3–5 locs.',   4,  10, 'var(--indigo)', 'Moderate · Review mix'],
  ['6–10 locs.',  7,  10, 'var(--amber)',  'High · Caution'],
  ['10+ locs.',  10,  10, 'var(--red)',    '✕ Avoid new supply'],
]);

renderNNBars('nnBars2', [
  ['0–2 locs.',  1,  10, 'var(--green)',  '✓ No tuck-in targets'],
  ['3–5 locs.',  4,  10, 'var(--blue)',   'Ideal tuck-in density'],
  ['6–9 locs.',  7,  10, 'var(--indigo)', 'Active market · Good'],
  ['10–14 locs.',11, 10, 'var(--amber)',  'Competitive · Qualify'],
  ['15+ locs.', 10,  10, 'var(--red)',    'Crowded tuck-in zone'],
]);

</script>
</body>
</html>
